  <body id="msgFeedSummaryBody" selected="false">
    <img typeof="foaf:Image" src="http://www.mediacurrent.com/sites/default/files/styles/thumb_blog_spotlight/public/design4drupal-01.png?itok=IHIMpkJ2" width="200" height="152" /> <p>Ever since the Drupal community started holding national regional conferences, dubbed DrupalCons and DrupalCamps, there has been a perception that design, usability and “theming” (i.e., managing HTML, CSS and JS output) were afterthoughts. And, to be honest, that has been true for many camps and conferences – while developers were geeking out on advanced Views API usage and performance tuning, those looking for a design focus were often left with introductory theming sessions.</p>
